{
  "video_id": "CxC161GvMPc",
  "title": "What is the tragedy of the commons? - Nicholas Amendolare",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 7694.0,
      "end_time": 11533.0,
      "text": "Imagine as a thought experiment that you live in a small village"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 11534.0,
      "end_time": 15102.0,
      "text": "and depend on  the local fish pond for food."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 15102.0,
      "end_time": 18710.0,
      "text": "You share the pond  with three other villagers."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18710.0,
      "end_time": 23412.0,
      "text": "The pond starts off with a dozen fish, and the fish reproduce."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23412.0,
      "end_time": 27855.0,
      "text": "For every two fish, there will be  one baby added each night."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27856.0,
      "end_time": 30424.0,
      "text": "So, in order to maximize  your supply of food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30424.0,
      "end_time": 34266.0,
      "text": "how many fish should you catch each day?"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34266.0,
      "end_time": 36596.0,
      "text": "Take a moment to think about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36596.0,
      "end_time": 39846.0,
      "text": "Assume baby fish grow  to full size immediately"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39847.0,
      "end_time": 42866.0,
      "text": "and that the pond begins at full capacity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42866.0,
      "end_time": 46726.0,
      "text": "and ignore factors  like the sex of the fish you catch."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 46726.0,
      "end_time": 50756.0,
      "text": "The answer? One, and it&#39;s not just you."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 50756.0,
      "end_time": 53707.0,
      "text": "The best way to maximize  every villager&#39;s food supply"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53707.0,
      "end_time": 58437.0,
      "text": "is for each fisherman to take  just one fish each day."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 58437.0,
      "end_time": 60108.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s how the math works."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 60108.0,
      "end_time": 64733.0,
      "text": "If each villager takes one fish, there will be eight fish left over night."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 64733.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67116.0,
      "text": "Each pair of fish produces one baby,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 67117.0,
      "end_time": 72187.0,
      "text": "and the next day, the pond  will be fully restocked with twelve fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 72187.0,
      "end_time": 77499.0,
      "text": "If anyone takes more than one, the number of reproductive pairs drops,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 77499.0,
      "end_time": 82408.0,
      "text": "and the population  won&#39;t be able to bounce back."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 82408.0,
      "end_time": 85149.0,
      "text": "Eventually, the fish in the lake  will be gone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 85149.0,
      "end_time": 88699.0,
      "text": "leaving all four villagers to starve."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 88699.0,
      "end_time": 91859.0,
      "text": "This fish pond is just one example of a classic problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 91859.0,
      "end_time": 94937.0,
      "text": "called the tragedy of the commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 94937.0,
      "end_time": 97508.0,
      "text": "The phenomenon was first described  in a pamphlet"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 97508.0,
      "end_time": 102176.0,
      "text": "by economist  William Forster Lloyd in 1833"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 102177.0,
      "end_time": 104749.0,
      "text": "in a discussion of  the overgrazing of cattle"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 104749.0,
      "end_time": 107788.0,
      "text": "on village common areas."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 107788.0,
      "end_time": 112628.0,
      "text": "More than 100 years later, ecologist Garrett Hardin revived the concept"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 112628.0,
      "end_time": 115358.0,
      "text": "to describe what happens  when many individuals"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 115358.0,
      "end_time": 118200.0,
      "text": "all share a limited resource,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 118200.0,
      "end_time": 119689.0,
      "text": "like grazing land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 119689.0,
      "end_time": 120791.0,
      "text": "fishing areas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 120792.0,
      "end_time": 121889.0,
      "text": "living space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 121889.0,
      "end_time": 123940.0,
      "text": "even clean air."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 123940.0,
      "end_time": 128380.0,
      "text": "Hardin argued that these situations pit short-term self-interest"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 128380.0,
      "end_time": 130249.0,
      "text": "against the common good,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 130249.0,
      "end_time": 132741.0,
      "text": "and they end badly for everyone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 132741.0,
      "end_time": 134140.0,
      "text": "resulting in overgrazing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 134140.0,
      "end_time": 135178.0,
      "text": "overfishing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 135179.0,
      "end_time": 136489.0,
      "text": "overpopulation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 136489.0,
      "end_time": 137560.0,
      "text": "pollution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 137560.0,
      "end_time": 140760.0,
      "text": "and other social  and environmental problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 140760.0,
      "end_time": 143269.0,
      "text": "The key feature of  a tragedy of the commons"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 143270.0,
      "end_time": 148600.0,
      "text": "is that it provides an opportunity for an individual to benefit him or herself"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 148600.0,
      "end_time": 153872.0,
      "text": "while spreading out any negative effects  across the larger population."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 153872.0,
      "end_time": 157107.0,
      "text": "To see what that means, let&#39;s revisit our fish pond."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 157107.0,
      "end_time": 159691.0,
      "text": "Each individual fisherman is motivated"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 159691.0,
      "end_time": 162952.0,
      "text": "to take as many fish  as he can for himself."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 162952.0,
      "end_time": 165571.0,
      "text": "Meanwhile, any decline  in fish reproduction"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 165571.0,
      "end_time": 168762.0,
      "text": "is shared by the entire village."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 168762.0,
      "end_time": 171453.0,
      "text": "Anxious to avoid  losing out to his neighbors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 171453.0,
      "end_time": 176403.0,
      "text": "a fisherman will conclude that it&#39;s in his best interest to take an extra fish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 176403.0,
      "end_time": 177242.0,
      "text": "or two,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 177242.0,
      "end_time": 178643.0,
      "text": "or three."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 178643.0,
      "end_time": 182591.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, this is the same conclusion reached by the other fisherman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 182591.0,
      "end_time": 184430.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s the tragedy."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 184430.0,
      "end_time": 190419.0,
      "text": "Optimizing for the self in the short term isn&#39;t optimal for anyone in the long term."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 190419.0,
      "end_time": 193303.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a simplified example, but the tragedy of the commons"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 193303.0,
      "end_time": 197864.0,
      "text": "plays out in the more complex systems of real life, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 197864.0,
      "end_time": 202783.0,
      "text": "The overuse of antibiotics has led to short-term gains in livestock production"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 202783.0,
      "end_time": 205230.0,
      "text": "and in treating common illnesses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 205230.0,
      "end_time": 210300.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s also resulted in the evolution of antibiotic-resistant bacteria,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 210300.0,
      "end_time": 212843.0,
      "text": "which threaten the entire population."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 212843.0,
      "end_time": 216465.0,
      "text": "A coal-fired power plant produces cheap electricity for its customers"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 216466.0,
      "end_time": 218563.0,
      "text": "and profits for its owners."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 218563.0,
      "end_time": 221225.0,
      "text": "These local benefits are helpful in the short term,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 221225.0,
      "end_time": 226984.0,
      "text": "but pollution from mining and burning coal is spread across the entire atmosphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 226985.0,
      "end_time": 229968.0,
      "text": "and sticks around for thousands of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 229968.0,
      "end_time": 232107.0,
      "text": "There are other examples, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 232108.0,
      "end_time": 233240.0,
      "text": "Littering,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 233240.0,
      "end_time": 234188.0,
      "text": "water shortages,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 234188.0,
      "end_time": 235494.0,
      "text": "deforestation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 235495.0,
      "end_time": 236728.0,
      "text": "traffic jams,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 236728.0,
      "end_time": 239541.0,
      "text": "even the purchase of bottled water."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 239541.0,
      "end_time": 245295.0,
      "text": "But human civilization has proven it&#39;s capable of doing something remarkable."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 245295.0,
      "end_time": 246785.0,
      "text": "We form social contracts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 246785.0,
      "end_time": 248595.0,
      "text": "we make communal agreements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 248595.0,
      "end_time": 250146.0,
      "text": "we elect governments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 250146.0,
      "end_time": 251994.0,
      "text": "and we pass laws."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 251995.0,
      "end_time": 257616.0,
      "text": "All this to save our collective selves from our own individual impulses."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 257616.0,
      "end_time": 262186.0,
      "text": "It isn&#39;t easy, and we certainly  don&#39;t get it right nearly all of the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 262186.0,
      "end_time": 266995.0,
      "text": "But humans at our best have shown that we can solve these problems"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 266995.0,
      "end_time": 271337.0,
      "text": "and we can continue to do so if we remember Hardin&#39;s lesson."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 271337.0,
      "end_time": 273866.0,
      "text": "When the tragedy of the commons applies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 273866.0,
      "end_time": 277265.0,
      "text": "what&#39;s good for all of us  is good for each of us."
    }
  ]
}